C:\Data\Nucleus_Dev\Vostok_ACU_A\source\XCategory\Application\all\Reveal_Basic\API010PollVar\API010PollVar.c
      1          /**
      2           * @file
      3           * @brief       Communications to get periodic publication of system and memory-mapped variables
      4           *
      5           * @details     API 010 Poll Variables is used to publish standard and custom variables for the
      6           *              purposes of data acquisition.
      7           *
      8           *              Fixed Variables:
      9           *              Fixed variables are standard variables that are defined for a specific Product
     10           *              Type. Some boards (such as expansion boards) may not support any standard
     11           *              variables. Use OpCode 21 to determine what is supported. These standard variables
     12           *              make it easier to quickly get up and running with a system that can monitor the
     13           *              basic variables of a product.
     14           *
     15           *              Memory-Mapped Variables:
     16           *              Memory-mapped variables allow a user to customize the data being monitored. Since
     17           *              memory-mapped variables are a compile-time option in the firmware, some boards
     18           *              may not support memory-mapped variables. Use OpCode 21 to determine what is
     19           *              supported. To add a memory-mapped variable to the list of monitored variables,
     20           *              the user must know the address and size of the variable.
     21           *
     22              @startuml{API010Publisher_sm.png}
     23                  title API 10 Publisher State Machine
     24                  ' terminate function unused
     25          
     26                  [*] --> Inactive
     27          
     28                  Inactive : entry / ResetPublisher()
     29                  Inactive : do / CheckMetadataDue()
     30                  Inactive --> Active : Enable_Publishing
     31          
     32                  Active : do / UpdateTimer()\n\t CheckDataDue()
     33                  Active --> Inactive : Disable_Publishing
     34                  Active --> Publishing : Start_Publishing
     35          
     36                  Publishing : entry / PublishNextPacket()
     37                  Publishing : do / UpdateTimer()\n\t PublishNextPacket()
     38                  Publishing --> Active : Stop_Publishing
     39                  Publishing --> Inactive : Disable_Publishing
     40              @enduml
     41           *
     42           * @copyright   Copyright 2014-2017 Whirlpool Corporation.  All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL.
     43           */
     44          /*lint -e9070
     45              Suppress Note: [9070]: recursive function 'Symbol', location Location
     46          
     47              A sequence of state transitions starting at a state and ending at the same state can represent
     48              an out-of-control recursive function. This can only happen if each state has an entry function
     49              that supports the endless loop.
     50          
     51              The API 10 Publisher state machine does not have a loop that does not involve the Active state
     52              and the Active state does not have an entry function. Therefore, this note can be suppressed.
     53          */
     54          
